{"id":"3938f605-f141-4e92-92de-72d620a94239","title":"1512/04/12","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"4972e375-10b3-4b93-a022-d05b57ba3e5d","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"12th April. We heard that the papal and Spanish armies were defeated by the French, and 10 thousand men slain,\u00A0two-thirds Spanish and one-third French. About 22 French lords were killed, and amongst them a nephew of the king, who many said had been our enemy: but perhaps it was not so. And it was said that if the French had not used so much artillery, which destroyed many hundreds of men-at-arms and cavalry, they would have been worsted. This was on the 11th April, the day of the Pasqua di Resurresso (Easter Day), near Ravenna, where the level had been made; and they had shattered one another in such a way, that although the French were victorious, nevertheless both armies were dispersed, and could do no harm to Florence, and the Spaniards might be thankful that they could go away without being plundered. Those who went through Romagna were plundered and even slain; but none of those who came through our territories had a hair of their head touched. They all went down to Rome, and the French went in the direction of Milan. ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"7a165e5b-634b-4a9e-86a0-8617ee004bed","type":"page","start":0,"end":110,"value":"250","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"855975ed-96fb-47d3-9ba9-cef5c63cc8df","type":"codex/time-reference","start":0,"end":9,"value":"f01e2818-0dbc-4d30-8574-6ed53f308725","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"bb499311-6639-43a9-b8d7-55a09d5a65b7","type":"style/superscript","start":2,"end":3,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c1c5fdde-1ed6-4c42-be7d-b26fdfb79ce6","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":12,"end":13,"value":"f219551f-c528-4666-8ada-4b95b7476b58","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"0428d6bc-5cc7-4983-89bd-b0c4585bd130","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":76,"end":81,"value":"80a4384f-f98a-47b2-aacb-7af